1
00:02:00,876 --> 00:02:03,868
<i>[Fireworks Bursting]</i>

2
00:02:15,824 --> 00:02:17,519
<i>[Muffled Groan]</i>

3
00:02:25,701 --> 00:02:28,067
[Gasping]

4
00:02:47,022 --> 00:02:50,924
- <i>[Gunshot Echoing]</i>
- Mr. Simmons! Do you have a confession?

5
00:02:50,993 --> 00:02:52,927
There were three shots.

6
00:02:52,995 --> 00:02:56,658
One grazed the shoulder,
a shot to the body, slug to the head.

7
00:02:56,732 --> 00:02:59,223
- It was a crime of passion.
- [Reporters Clamoring]

8
00:02:59,301 --> 00:03:02,236
<i>Mr. Simmons, how is this case gonna</i>
<i>impact your political career?</i>

9
00:03:02,304 --> 00:03:05,967
We'll hold
a press conference shortly...

10
00:03:06,041 --> 00:03:08,635
and I'll respond
to all your questions then.

11
00:03:08,710 --> 00:03:12,146
- <i>Can you tell us anything else about the suspect?</i>
- <i>Are you guilty, Mrs. Mass?</i>

12
00:03:12,214 --> 00:03:17,083
Hey, Bill. Detective Hicks here will
assist with the interrogation.

13
00:03:17,152 --> 00:03:19,848
- You mean the lynching?
- Counselor Miller.

14
00:03:19,921 --> 00:03:22,947
Dwight. Listen, we all know
that you're up for your boss's job.

15
00:03:23,025 --> 00:03:27,257
But let me ask you a question-
Is the truth getting in the way here?

16
00:03:27,329 --> 00:03:31,459
<i>Are we being recorded or videotaped?</i>
<i>If we are, I'm gonna suggest my client say nothing.</i>

17
00:03:31,533 --> 00:03:34,161
[Simmons]
Richard, don't make this thing complicated.

18
00:03:34,236 --> 00:03:37,000
We have a motive- infidelity.

19
00:03:37,072 --> 00:03:40,530
<i>Access to the murder scene.</i>
<i>Prints on the murder weapon.</i>

20
00:03:40,609 --> 00:03:45,808
Earrings- <i>her</i> earrings-
found at the scene. No alibi.

21
00:03:45,881 --> 00:03:49,282
We got the Holy Trinity-
probable cause, access, motive.

22
00:03:49,351 --> 00:03:52,013
Let's be reasonable here.
I'm willing to make a deal.

23
00:03:52,087 --> 00:03:53,952
No deals.

24
00:03:54,022 --> 00:03:56,684
I'm innocent.

25
00:03:56,758 --> 00:04:00,216
I'm a Christian, not a murderer.

26
00:04:02,464 --> 00:04:06,992
Ah. Oh, Mr. Simmons,
I'm not the negotiator that you are...

27
00:04:07,069 --> 00:04:10,334
<i>but would you mind letting me</i>
<i>have a few moments with Ms. Mass here?</i>

28
00:04:10,405 --> 00:04:14,398
- <i>Go ahead, Detective.</i>
- Oh, I see. This is going to be a team effort.

29
00:04:14,476 --> 00:04:17,809
I'm gonna need that confession.

30
00:04:17,879 --> 00:04:20,473
- Time.
- Mm-hmm.

31
00:04:20,549 --> 00:04:23,746
He's got a press conference.
We don't have a whole lot of time.

32
00:04:23,819 --> 00:04:28,153
- That's not our problem.
- Oh, yeah, but it is. It is.

33
00:04:28,223 --> 00:04:30,214
Now, you playin'
the Christian card-

34
00:04:30,292 --> 00:04:33,022
<i>good old God-fearin' black woman.</i>

35
00:04:33,095 --> 00:04:35,689
- Miss Spelman College.
- Don't patronize me.

36
00:04:35,764 --> 00:04:38,528
Hey, hey, hey. It's not me that you
should be worried about.

37
00:04:38,600 --> 00:04:41,660
It's the jury that you
should be worried about.

38
00:04:41,736 --> 00:04:45,172
With not the slightest
hint of remorse, confession...

39
00:04:45,240 --> 00:04:50,041
that jury just might give
a spiritual woman like yourself...

40
00:04:50,112 --> 00:04:52,774
a free ticket to heaven-
courtesy of the state.

41
00:04:52,848 --> 00:04:55,783
- <i>Detective.</i>
- <i>Hmm?</i>

42
00:04:55,851 --> 00:04:59,548
- Do you go to church?
- Oh, yeah. C.M.E.

43
00:04:59,621 --> 00:05:02,715
Christmas, Mother's Day and Easter.

44
00:05:02,791 --> 00:05:05,191
<i>Valerie, you don't have</i>
<i>to respond to any of this.</i>

45
00:05:05,260 --> 00:05:07,251
You're not on trial here.

46
00:05:08,597 --> 00:05:13,591
I'm not worried,
and I have nothin' to hide.

47
00:05:13,668 --> 00:05:16,068
But I must be allowed
to tell everything.

48
00:05:19,007 --> 00:05:20,998
Fine.
[Clears Throat]

49
00:05:23,378 --> 00:05:25,369
How long is everything gonna take?

50
00:05:26,815 --> 00:05:28,908
Before I was accused of murder...

51
00:05:30,819 --> 00:05:33,344
before my family
was ripped apart-

52
00:05:33,522 --> 00:05:35,956
- <i>## [Car Stereo: Hip-hop]</i>
- <i>[Child Shouts]</i>

53
00:05:39,828 --> 00:05:42,729
Aw, Philly's all right.

54
00:05:42,797 --> 00:05:44,765
Yeah, but I got big dreams,
you know?

55
00:05:44,833 --> 00:05:46,926
Whoa!
The prettiest girl in the world.

56
00:05:47,002 --> 00:05:48,936
Huh?
[Chuckling]

57
00:05:49,004 --> 00:05:51,939
- Hey!
- What's up?

58
00:05:52,007 --> 00:05:53,998
- <i>## [Stereo: Soul]</i>
- Hey, girl. Hey, Daddy.

59
00:05:54,075 --> 00:05:56,168
- Everything good?
- Yes, girl.

60
00:05:56,244 --> 00:05:58,178
- Practically all moved in.
- Good.

61
00:05:58,246 --> 00:06:01,409
- So, how's the new place?
- Oh, it's nice. It's nice.

62
00:06:01,483 --> 00:06:03,576
- It ain't big-
- [Slaps Butt] Watch out now.

63
00:06:03,652 --> 00:06:05,643
<i>[Laughing]</i>
<i>It's not big, but you know.</i>

64
00:06:05,720 --> 00:06:08,655
Girl, you deserve the best,
and that's exactly what you gonna get.

65
00:06:08,723 --> 00:06:11,658
What I need right now is a church.

66
00:06:11,726 --> 00:06:14,126
I told you, you are
gonna love Mercy Baptist.

67
00:06:14,196 --> 00:06:16,926
- All right, well, I'm ready to go now.
- All right then.

68
00:06:16,998 --> 00:06:19,023
- I'm late for work. I'll hit you later.
- All right.

69
00:06:19,100 --> 00:06:22,126
<i>Grandpa!</i>
<i>Are you helping us?</i>

70
00:06:22,204 --> 00:06:25,605
- Shh! Forget that "Grandpa" stuff now.
- <i>[Man] Go on inside.</i>

71
00:06:25,674 --> 00:06:27,039
- Don't look at that.
- [Chuckling]

72
00:06:27,108 --> 00:06:30,669
Daddy and Grandpa
are looking at B-U-T-T-S.

73
00:06:30,745 --> 00:06:32,770
- Whoa, whoa!
- Uh-huh.

74
00:06:32,847 --> 00:06:36,681
It's nice that you had such a warm
and fuzzy reception, but is this relevant?

75
00:06:36,751 --> 00:06:40,380
We're not gonna be railroaded just because
your boss has a press conference.

76
00:06:40,455 --> 00:06:43,856
Val, anything you say, they can take
and twist it any way that they want.

77
00:06:43,925 --> 00:06:45,859
<i>A jury can be manipulated.</i>

78
00:06:45,927 --> 00:06:47,986
I have nothing to hide.

79
00:06:48,063 --> 00:06:51,032
And, yes, Detective Hicks,
everything I'm about to tell you-

80
00:06:51,099 --> 00:06:53,533
it's all relevant.

81
00:06:53,602 --> 00:06:56,230
[Woman]
So, I took a look at your portfolio. Looks good.

82
00:06:56,304 --> 00:06:58,670
<i>I'm gonna recommend you for some</i>
<i>photo shoots we got comin' up.</i>

83
00:06:58,740 --> 00:07:01,004
- Are you serious?
- Am I serious?

84
00:07:01,076 --> 00:07:03,067
- Don't play with me.
- I ain't playin' with you.

85
00:07:03,144 --> 00:07:05,977
- [Exclaims]
- Chill it out. It's nothin' immediate.

86
00:07:06,047 --> 00:07:09,244
- <i>But I'm definitely down for hookin' my girl up.</i>
- <i>All right.</i>

87
00:07:09,317 --> 00:07:12,411
That's a real sacrifice-you givin' up
your studio for your husband's career.

88
00:07:12,487 --> 00:07:15,081
- You're so old-fashioned.
- [Laughs]

89
00:07:15,156 --> 00:07:18,614
Well, I love my husband.

90
00:07:18,693 --> 00:07:21,059
And, Zahara, he's worth it.

91
00:07:21,129 --> 00:07:24,496
- [Man] What's up, baby?
- Dog! You see there?

92
00:07:24,566 --> 00:07:26,659
All men are dogs.
All they need are fleas.

93
00:07:26,735 --> 00:07:28,669
And I met one last week
who had some.

94
00:07:28,737 --> 00:07:31,672
So tell me about
Mercy Baptist, girl.

95
00:07:31,740 --> 00:07:33,674
Oh, it's a nice church.

96
00:07:33,742 --> 00:07:37,041
Reverend Dunn and his wife, they don't
just talk the talk. They walk the walk.

97
00:07:37,112 --> 00:07:40,047
<i>They feed homeless folks,</i>
<i>teach H.I. V. prevention.</i>

98
00:07:40,115 --> 00:07:44,848
- Monday nights-women's group.
Fabulous. You must join us.
- <i>I'll be there.</i>

99
00:07:44,919 --> 00:07:47,513
Now, Reverend Dunn starts
Sunday services at 10:00 a.m. sharp.

100
00:07:47,589 --> 00:07:49,716
So none of that Delta C.T.P. time.

101
00:07:49,791 --> 00:07:53,784
[Laughs]
No. <i>C.P.</i> time.

102
00:07:53,862 --> 00:07:55,853
<i>And you can't say it right</i>
<i>'cause you're wrong.</i>

103
00:07:55,930 --> 00:07:58,558
You never would've made it to class
on time if it weren't for me.

104
00:07:58,633 --> 00:08:02,262
- Whatever, Miss Delta.
- <i>That's right, "crimson and cream'"baby.</i>

105
00:08:02,337 --> 00:08:05,932
- <i>Uh-uh. Pink and green-girls with the pearls.</i>
- [Both Laughing]

106
00:08:06,007 --> 00:08:09,238
- Dog!
- Girl, he didn't say nothin' to you.

107
00:08:09,311 --> 00:08:13,213
- He was thinkin' 'bout it.
- [Both Laughing]

108
00:08:13,281 --> 00:08:15,943
For Dutch...

109
00:08:16,017 --> 00:08:18,417
the move from Atlanta
was no big deal.

110
00:08:18,486 --> 00:08:21,080
You know,
he grew up in Philadelphia.

111
00:08:22,524 --> 00:08:24,549
But for me...

112
00:08:24,626 --> 00:08:27,459
it was a place where all
our dreams would come true.

113
00:08:30,865 --> 00:08:33,732
It never occurred to me
that nightmares are dreams too.

114
00:08:33,802 --> 00:08:38,637
"'W hat do we have here? ' snarled the huge wolf."
[Snarls Tamely]

115
00:08:38,707 --> 00:08:41,198
- Not good enough.
- What?

116
00:08:41,276 --> 00:08:43,210
- I'm warning you.
- Mm-mmm.

117
00:08:43,278 --> 00:08:48,409
Come on. " 'W hat do we have here? '
snarled the huge wolf."

118
00:08:48,483 --> 00:08:50,610
[Snarling]

119
00:08:50,685 --> 00:08:53,313
Not good enough.

120
00:08:53,388 --> 00:08:56,255
- I think we need to-
- Yeah.

121
00:08:56,324 --> 00:08:58,792
[Together]
One, two-

122
00:08:58,860 --> 00:09:00,794
- What? Come on.
- three!

123
00:09:00,862 --> 00:09:02,887
- [Both Shrieking]
- Come on.

124
00:09:04,065 --> 00:09:06,056
I put the gun in my mouth.

125
00:09:08,136 --> 00:09:11,469
I started to... pull the trigger.

126
00:09:16,211 --> 00:09:20,045
I saw my daughter's face... crying.

127
00:09:24,419 --> 00:09:26,751
Then I realized...

128
00:09:26,821 --> 00:09:28,812
how selfish I was being.

129
00:09:30,458 --> 00:09:34,189
Some days, everything matters.

130
00:09:34,262 --> 00:09:36,822
Some days, nothin' matters.

131
00:09:39,634 --> 00:09:41,625
I want you
to make a commitment-

132
00:09:41,703 --> 00:09:43,967
every day for the next 30 days.

133
00:09:44,038 --> 00:09:46,472
Deal?

134
00:09:49,778 --> 00:09:52,212
I'll see you tomorrow, same time.

135
00:09:52,280 --> 00:09:54,748
- Thank you, Doctor.
- My pleasure.

136
00:09:56,317 --> 00:09:59,252
- [Exhales]
- <i>[Knocking]</i>

137
00:09:59,320 --> 00:10:02,915
- Monica.
- Dutch. Good to see you.

138
00:10:02,991 --> 00:10:05,721
- I'm sorry I wasn't here when you arrived.
- Oh.

139
00:10:05,794 --> 00:10:09,321
I was at a conference. I'm late for
a meeting, but I need to talk to you.

140
00:10:09,397 --> 00:10:12,764
- Can you walk with me?
- Yeah. Yeah.

141
00:10:12,834 --> 00:10:15,268
It appears your time
at Oxford has paid off.

142
00:10:15,336 --> 00:10:18,703
You've even picked up an accent.
Good for business.

143
00:10:18,773 --> 00:10:21,435
I know a mind
is a terrible thing to waste.

144
00:10:21,509 --> 00:10:23,704
- How are you and Kevin?
- Miserable, as usual.

145
00:10:23,778 --> 00:10:25,769
But I might as well
get to the point.

146
00:10:25,847 --> 00:10:28,077
We won't be able to pay
the salary you requested.

147
00:10:28,149 --> 00:10:30,617
I "requested"? Oh, you mean
the salary you promised me.

148
00:10:30,685 --> 00:10:32,585
No one's deceived you.
The offer was-

149
00:10:32,654 --> 00:10:36,181
I moved my family up here from Atlanta.
Now you're telling me there's no money?

150
00:10:36,257 --> 00:10:38,088
Every contract has contingencies-

151
00:10:38,159 --> 00:10:40,286
subject to pending grants
and all the fine print.

152
00:10:40,361 --> 00:10:42,727
But that's beside the point.
I want you here.

153
00:10:42,797 --> 00:10:45,231
And I will do everything in my power
to keep you here.

154
00:10:45,300 --> 00:10:47,291
Like old times, right?

155
00:10:49,003 --> 00:10:52,268
Monica, that's inappropriate.
I'm happily married.

156
00:10:52,340 --> 00:10:55,741
- Happily, so am I.
- To one of my best friends.

157
00:10:55,810 --> 00:10:59,610
As if Kevin would mind.
Nothing's changed.

158
00:10:59,681 --> 00:11:02,013
We need to have
this conversation later.

159
00:11:02,083 --> 00:11:04,074
Come to our surprise
anniversary party.

160
00:11:04,152 --> 00:11:06,746
It's Sunday afternoon
at the Academy of Fine Arts.

161
00:11:06,821 --> 00:11:09,415
How can it be a surprise
when you already know about it?

162
00:11:09,491 --> 00:11:12,358
There are no secrets between us, Dutch.
You know that.

163
00:11:12,427 --> 00:11:14,418
Ryan Chambers is hosting it for us.

164
00:11:14,496 --> 00:11:16,589
I'm sorry.
We go to church on Sunday.

165
00:11:16,664 --> 00:11:19,929
Your presence is required,
not requested, Dr. Mass.

166
00:11:20,969 --> 00:11:23,062
<i>[Woman]</i>
<i>#Praise the Lord #

167
00:11:23,137 --> 00:11:25,264
<i># Come on, come on #

168
00:11:25,340 --> 00:11:27,308
<i># Come on, come on #

169
00:11:27,375 --> 00:11:29,309
<i># Come by me #

170
00:11:29,377 --> 00:11:32,642
# O Lord, come by me #

171
00:11:32,714 --> 00:11:37,742
- ## [Vocalizing]
- # O Lord, come by me #

172
00:11:37,819 --> 00:11:40,515
- [Woman Shouting]
- Whoo! Yeah! Come on! Sing! Yeah!

173
00:11:40,588 --> 00:11:42,351
<i># Yeah #

174
00:11:42,423 --> 00:11:46,826
## [Vocalizing]

175
00:11:46,895 --> 00:11:48,920
Hallelujah!

176
00:11:48,997 --> 00:11:51,761
- Thank God!
- # Ooh #

177
00:11:51,833 --> 00:11:53,858
- <i>## [Ends]</i>
- Praise God!

178
00:11:53,935 --> 00:11:56,369
- Let the church say "Amen!"
- [Congregation] Amen!

179
00:11:56,437 --> 00:11:58,132
- <i>[Reverend] Yes!</i>
- <i>[Woman] Hallelujah!</i>

180
00:11:58,206 --> 00:12:02,768
I'm talkin' about the land
of the designer walk and the designer talk.

181
00:12:02,844 --> 00:12:06,780
<i>The designer gowns</i>
<i>and the designer frowns.</i>

182
00:12:06,848 --> 00:12:11,217
- [Congregation Exclaiming]
- Designer husbands, designer wives.

183
00:12:11,286 --> 00:12:13,846
Designer smiles, designer styles.

184
00:12:13,922 --> 00:12:17,881
<i>All designed by the one who knows...</i>

185
00:12:17,959 --> 00:12:21,360
the weakness of the flesh
is temptation.

186
00:12:21,429 --> 00:12:25,331
- <i>[Applause, Exclaiming]</i>
- <i>The flesh may call your name...</i>

187
00:12:25,400 --> 00:12:27,834
but only God can call your soul!

188
00:12:27,902 --> 00:12:30,803
[Shouting, Exclaiming]

189
00:12:30,872 --> 00:12:33,238
<i>Only God can call your soul!</i>

190
00:12:35,243 --> 00:12:39,009
- <i>Yes! Surrender, rich man.</i>
- <i>[Woman] Hallelujah!</i>

191
00:12:39,080 --> 00:12:41,605
Surrender, poor man.

192
00:12:41,683 --> 00:12:45,551
Surrender, beggar man.
Surrender, thief.

193
00:12:45,620 --> 00:12:48,088
- <i>[Woman] Praise the Lord!</i>
- Surrender.

194
00:12:48,156 --> 00:12:52,252
When God calls you, surrender,
adulterer.

195
00:12:52,327 --> 00:12:54,261
Surrender, liar.

196
00:12:54,329 --> 00:12:58,322
<i>Surrender, kings,</i>
<i>the presidents and Indian chiefs.</i>

197
00:12:58,399 --> 00:13:00,663
- <i>[Man] Amen!</i>
- Surrender!

198
00:13:00,735 --> 00:13:05,297
- The time is drawing near for you to surrender.
- <i>[Woman] Glory be to God!</i>

199
00:13:05,373 --> 00:13:07,671
Surrender.

200
00:13:07,742 --> 00:13:10,575
- Thank you, Heavenly Father.
- Yes.

201
00:13:10,645 --> 00:13:15,981
Now, anyone who wants
to join the church this morning...

202
00:13:16,050 --> 00:13:19,076
please come down to the altar.

203
00:13:19,153 --> 00:13:21,951
Let him know.
Let him know.

204
00:13:22,023 --> 00:13:24,514
- <i>[Woman] Yes, God!</i>
- Let him know.

205
00:13:24,592 --> 00:13:28,551
Whoever you are, let him know.
Come down.

206
00:13:28,630 --> 00:13:31,190
Come on, Dutch.
You ready? Let's go.

207
00:13:31,265 --> 00:13:33,392
- I'm not goin'.
- Why not?

208
00:13:33,468 --> 00:13:36,403
- I just can't.
- Dutch.

209
00:13:36,471 --> 00:13:39,804
- Go.
- Is Daddy coming?

210
00:13:39,874 --> 00:13:43,537
- Daddy's gonna come next time.
- <i>[Reverend] Those of you in pain.</i>

211
00:13:43,611 --> 00:13:47,047
- <i>Those of you in confusion.</i>
- Hallelujah.

212
00:13:47,115 --> 00:13:52,075
- <i>[Woman] Amen!</i>
- <i>Those of you in deceit and despair.</i>

213
00:13:52,153 --> 00:13:55,020
<i>[Reverend Continues,</i>
<i>Indistinct]</i>

214
00:13:58,326 --> 00:14:00,817
<i>[Valerie]</i>
<i>Dutch, I'm not thinking about this right now.</i>

215
00:14:00,895 --> 00:14:02,886
I can't believe you did that today.

216
00:14:02,964 --> 00:14:06,127
[Sighs]
There you go. Faith won't pay the bills.

217
00:14:06,200 --> 00:14:08,862
What does that have
to do with you joining church?

218
00:14:08,936 --> 00:14:11,336
Do we have to talk
about this now, here?

219
00:14:11,406 --> 00:14:13,931
You don't want me to embarrass you
