01:19:37,364 --> 01:19:41,460
Then get on your knees, and don't get off
until you've found the answer.

1316
01:19:41,535 --> 01:19:43,059
You judging me?

1317
01:19:43,136 --> 01:19:47,129
What happened to judge
not lest ye be judged?

1318
01:19:47,207 --> 01:19:49,198
What happened to that?

1319
01:19:54,581 --> 01:19:56,708
I'm not judging you, son.

1320
01:19:56,783 --> 01:20:01,083
I do have a question. Are you saying
that what you did was right?

1321
01:20:01,154 --> 01:20:05,955
No. I'm not saying I was right.

1322
01:20:06,026 --> 01:20:08,494
But maybe I did the best I could.

1323
01:20:08,562 --> 01:20:10,496
You believe that?

1324
01:20:10,564 --> 01:20:13,465
How far you think that's
gonna fly with the Lord?

1325
01:20:13,533 --> 01:20:17,469
It's cruel and selfish to bring
a possible death sentence...

1326
01:20:17,537 --> 01:20:20,904
to those you say you love
for a few moments...

1327
01:20:20,974 --> 01:20:22,942
of lust and pleasure.

1328
01:20:23,009 --> 01:20:26,035
You think I don't know that?

1329
01:20:26,112 --> 01:20:29,206
Yeah, I'm a coward...

1330
01:20:30,750 --> 01:20:32,741
and I'm afraid.

1331
01:20:34,354 --> 01:20:37,482
What would have happened
if I'd been honest?

1332
01:20:40,393 --> 01:20:42,384
I'd be called a sinner.

1333
01:20:42,462 --> 01:20:48,423
A homo. A fag.
Do you know how hypocritical that is...

1334
01:20:48,501 --> 01:20:51,061
when you look at the D.L. brothers
in your own congregation?

1335
01:20:51,137 --> 01:20:55,836
Are you suggesting that the imperfection
of the sinners in my church...

1336
01:20:55,909 --> 01:20:59,572
is the reason you betrayed
your wife and child?

1337
01:21:00,981 --> 01:21:05,111
I'm used to people lying to me, son.

1338
01:21:05,185 --> 01:21:08,313
You're lying to yourself.
That's the worst of it.

1339
01:21:08,388 --> 01:21:12,324
We both know that if I'd been honest,
I'd have lost everything.

1340
01:21:12,392 --> 01:21:17,159
I hate to break the news to you, son.
You lost everything.

1341
01:21:18,865 --> 01:21:21,891
- Except-
- Except what?

1342
01:21:21,968 --> 01:21:24,095
Redemption.

1343
01:21:25,905 --> 01:21:29,500
God don't hold grudges.

1344
01:21:29,576 --> 01:21:31,510
His hands is always
stretched out to us...

1345
01:21:31,578 --> 01:21:34,240
whether we're riding
the chariots of grace...

1346
01:21:34,314 --> 01:21:37,078
or crushed beneath the wheels.

1347
01:21:39,586 --> 01:21:43,955
He's there.
He's there waiting for you.

1348
01:21:44,024 --> 01:21:48,757
The longer you wait,
the harder it's gonna be.

1349
01:21:48,828 --> 01:21:51,023
But you have to call him.

1350
01:21:52,966 --> 01:21:54,957
Just call him, son.

1351
01:21:57,137 --> 01:21:59,401
Call him now.

1352
01:22:20,627 --> 01:22:24,085
<i>[Man]</i>
<i>Number 16. Number 16.</i>

1353
01:22:25,398 --> 01:22:26,990
- Hi.
- Hi.

1354
01:22:27,067 --> 01:22:29,035
[Clears Throat]
I'm here to be tested.

1355
01:22:29,102 --> 01:22:32,833
Take this number, and someone
will be with you as soon as possible.

1356
01:22:32,906 --> 01:22:34,897
- Thank you.
- Okay.

1357
01:22:36,676 --> 01:22:38,667
<i>[Man]</i>
<i>Number 17.</i>

1358
01:22:57,163 --> 01:22:59,256
<i>Number 18.</i>

1359
01:23:09,843 --> 01:23:13,370
Ms. Valerie Mass, your time is up,
and the offer's off the table.

1360
01:23:13,446 --> 01:23:15,414
- What are you talking about?
- You're being charged with first-degree murder.

1361
01:23:15,482 --> 01:23:18,849
<i>Are you out of your mind? Valerie,</i>
<i>I'll have you out of here in no time.</i>

1362
01:23:18,918 --> 01:23:23,617
- Detective Hicks, I'm innocent.
- I know you don't care about
this girl's guilt or innocence.

1363
01:23:23,690 --> 01:23:27,217
- Get out of my face.
- There's a long way between here and conviction...

1364
01:23:27,293 --> 01:23:29,261
<i>Assistant D.A.</i>

1365
01:23:29,329 --> 01:23:34,289
<i>And you tell me, where do you think you're</i>
<i>gonna be when this case blows up in your face?</i>

1366
01:23:36,903 --> 01:23:40,270
The election will be over by then.

1367
01:23:42,976 --> 01:23:44,967
<i>[Door Opens]</i>

1368
01:23:46,179 --> 01:23:48,306
<i>[Door Closes]</i>

1369
01:24:08,134 --> 01:24:10,295
Valerie Mass.
Number 225.

1370
01:24:23,049 --> 01:24:27,179
Ladies and gentlemen of the press,
I would like to-

1371
01:24:27,253 --> 01:24:29,721
<i>Excuse me.</i>

1372
01:24:31,524 --> 01:24:34,015
I'm sorry. We're going to have to delay
this press conference...

1373
01:24:34,093 --> 01:24:36,493
<i>for about five minutes or so.</i>

1374
01:24:36,563 --> 01:24:40,431
- [Reporters Clamoring]
- Now this is still a breaking story.

1375
01:24:40,500 --> 01:24:42,434
Can you tell us what happened,
Mr. Simmons?

1376
01:24:42,502 --> 01:24:46,233
This better be worth my while.
What exactly is on this DVD?

1377
01:24:46,306 --> 01:24:48,968
Well, I've only watched a few seconds,
and I already know...

1378
01:24:49,042 --> 01:24:52,273
that you can't go to the press conference
without checking this out.

1379
01:24:53,780 --> 01:24:57,443
This was delivered to the front desk
addressed to Valerie Mass.

1380
01:24:58,485 --> 01:25:00,385
- And who's it from?
- <i>"To Valerie Mass.</i>

1381
01:25:00,453 --> 01:25:05,356
A gift from me and my ex.
Charlotte Chambers."

1382
01:25:07,694 --> 01:25:10,891
- [Charlotte] Talk.
- What do you want me to say?

1383
01:25:10,964 --> 01:25:13,296
I am who I am.

1384
01:25:14,934 --> 01:25:18,893
Or if you're watching this-
[Chuckles] who I was.

1385
01:25:18,972 --> 01:25:20,803
What is this?

1386
01:25:20,874 --> 01:25:23,638
It's beginning to look like
that confession you wanted.

1387
01:25:23,710 --> 01:25:26,907
<i>[Ryan]</i>
<i>My death, like my life, will be spectacular.</i>

1388
01:25:26,980 --> 01:25:32,111
What do you do when someone
you trust gives you a gift?

1389
01:25:32,185 --> 01:25:35,245
A disease without any warning.

1390
01:25:35,321 --> 01:25:39,052
Well, you can't blame me
for wanting to share the gift.

1391
01:25:39,125 --> 01:25:41,958
Yes, I'm sorry.

1392
01:25:42,028 --> 01:25:45,020
But who is sorry for me?

1393
01:25:45,098 --> 01:25:49,626
For those of you I might
have hurt, what can I say?

1394
01:25:49,702 --> 01:25:52,102
Be more careful.

1395
01:25:52,171 --> 01:25:54,662
You never know where
the bogeyman is.

1396
01:25:56,409 --> 01:26:00,812
<i>And those of you who wanna</i>
<i>make judgment, hell, it ain't my fault.</i>

1397
01:26:00,880 --> 01:26:04,782
<i>You want guys like us</i>
<i>to be open and honest...</i>

1398
01:26:04,851 --> 01:26:08,446
<i>so you can publicly</i>
<i>humiliate us and condemn us.</i>

1399
01:26:08,521 --> 01:26:12,048
<i>I might be a coward,</i>
<i>but I ain't stupid.</i>

1400
01:26:12,125 --> 01:26:15,856
I will never let you
treat me like that. Never!

1401
01:26:15,929 --> 01:26:18,022
I'll play the monster.

1402
01:26:19,666 --> 01:26:21,691
And I'm just like you.

1403
01:26:23,136 --> 01:26:26,299
I never thought
it would happen to me.

1404
01:26:27,740 --> 01:26:30,675
- And, yes...
- <i>[Gun Cocks]</i>

1405
01:26:30,743 --> 01:26:33,268
the bogeyman is for real.

1406
01:26:33,346 --> 01:26:35,644
<i>[Gunshot]</i>

1407
01:26:37,817 --> 01:26:40,786
I'm gonna give you more
of a chance than you gave me.

1408
01:26:42,622 --> 01:26:44,613
[Gun Cocks]

1409
01:26:50,063 --> 01:26:51,724
Bravo.

1410
01:26:56,336 --> 01:26:58,270
Thank you, Detective.

1411
01:26:58,338 --> 01:27:00,306
Captain would be better.

1412
01:27:01,741 --> 01:27:03,675
Captain.

1413
01:27:07,714 --> 01:27:11,582
Well, I am pleased to announce
that after a vigorous...

1414
01:27:11,651 --> 01:27:14,017
<i>and thorough investigation...</i>

1415
01:27:14,087 --> 01:27:16,681
my department has freed
an innocent woman...

1416
01:27:16,756 --> 01:27:19,418
who was falsely accused
of first-degree murder.

1417
01:27:19,492 --> 01:27:22,518
- Now regardless of my political ambition-
- <i>## [Choir Vocalizing]</i>

1418
01:27:22,662 --> 01:27:27,497
<i>Thy kingdom come, thy will be done</i>
<i>on earth as it is in heaven.</i>

1419
01:27:27,567 --> 01:27:30,001
Give us this day our daily bread...

1420
01:27:30,069 --> 01:27:32,060
- [Siren Wailing]
- <i>and forgive us our trespasses...</i>

1421
01:27:32,138 --> 01:27:34,368
<i>as we forgive those</i>
<i>who trespass against us.</i>

1422
01:27:34,440 --> 01:27:37,170
<i>## [Vocalizing Continues]</i>

1423
01:27:38,911 --> 01:27:41,072
And lead us not into temptation-

1424
01:27:41,147 --> 01:27:45,311
For all of us, there is light.
But passion...

1425
01:27:45,385 --> 01:27:48,445
<i>without responsibility...</i>

1426
01:27:48,521 --> 01:27:51,285
<i>is not only</i>
<i>a self-destructive act...</i>

1427
01:27:51,357 --> 01:27:55,487
<i>but like the godless stone</i>
<i>of ignorance...</i>

1428
01:27:55,561 --> 01:27:58,052
<i>dropped in the rippling pond</i>
<i>of tragedy.</i>

1429
01:27:58,131 --> 01:28:00,998
<i>In this day and these times...</i>

1430
01:28:01,067 --> 01:28:05,367
<i>it can destroy</i>
<i>those we love the most.</i>

1431
01:28:05,438 --> 01:28:09,340
- <i>Charlotte's suicide will</i>
<i>not keep her from God's arms.</i>
- Thank you.

1432
01:28:09,409 --> 01:28:13,345
If a man does not seek humility...

1433
01:28:13,413 --> 01:28:15,938
<i>humility will seek man.</i>

1434
01:28:37,522 --> 01:28:39,513
Thank you for coming.

1435
01:28:41,426 --> 01:28:44,156
Are you okay?

1436
01:28:45,797 --> 01:28:49,961
It'll be good
to be back home again...

1437
01:28:50,035 --> 01:28:51,969
running my own studio.

1438
01:29:01,013 --> 01:29:03,777
<i>I just want you to know...</i>

1439
01:29:03,849 --> 01:29:07,216
that none of this is your fault.

1440
01:29:08,854 --> 01:29:11,914
<i>There's nothing</i>
<i>you could have done...</i>

1441
01:29:11,990 --> 01:29:14,982
<i>that would have made a difference.</i>

1442
01:29:19,398 --> 01:29:22,196
I've been tested and, uh...

1443
01:29:22,267 --> 01:29:25,065
they didn't find anything.

1444
01:29:25,137 --> 01:29:27,128
Same with me.

1445
01:29:31,576 --> 01:29:33,510
Val, I told you-

1446
01:29:33,578 --> 01:29:35,910
You know, I've been struggling with this.

1447
01:29:38,884 --> 01:29:40,852
Was I the friend
you needed me to be?

1448
01:29:40,919 --> 01:29:43,911
Was I the wife you needed me to be?

1449
01:29:43,989 --> 01:29:47,755
Was I the Christian
you needed me to be?

1450
01:29:50,529 --> 01:29:54,158
And... could you have stopped?

1451
01:29:58,170 --> 01:30:00,104
Could you?

1452
01:30:05,277 --> 01:30:07,404
I don't know.

1453
01:30:14,986 --> 01:30:16,977
I love you, Dutch.

1454
01:30:21,593 --> 01:30:25,552
But I can't...
trust you anymore.

1455
01:30:52,324 --> 01:30:54,986
- Daddy!
- <i>Hey, sweetheart.</i>

1456
01:30:58,430 --> 01:31:00,421
Oh!

1457
01:31:02,167 --> 01:31:04,362
I love you.

1458
01:31:04,436 --> 01:31:06,427
I love you more.

1459
01:31:10,709 --> 01:31:12,768
My beautiful girl.

1460
01:31:14,913 --> 01:31:16,676
- Be good. Okay?
- Okay.

1461
01:31:17,682 --> 01:31:19,547
Okay, go to Mama.

1462
01:31:34,766 --> 01:31:36,757
All right.

1463
01:31:42,774 --> 01:31:44,765
I love you, Son.

1464
01:32:44,336 --> 01:32:47,430
<i>[Knocking]</i>

1465
01:32:53,111 --> 01:32:55,671
Are you showing the house?

1466
01:32:57,849 --> 01:33:01,307
Not now. Uh, the Realtor
will be here tomorrow.

1467
01:33:01,386 --> 01:33:03,479
Why don't you come back then?

1468
01:33:03,555 --> 01:33:05,614
You hear that, baby?

1469
01:33:05,690 --> 01:33:09,148
We might have just found
the house of our dreams.

1470
01:33:09,227 --> 01:33:12,788
Hey, um, you mind
if I look around inside?

1471
01:33:12,864 --> 01:33:16,823
It's dusty around here. You look like
you got something in your eye.

1472
01:33:16,901 --> 01:33:19,426
What did you say?

1473
01:33:19,504 --> 01:33:23,565
I think you got something in your eye.
You want me to blow it out for you?

1474
01:33:30,081 --> 01:33:32,072
Hey.

1475
01:33:33,652 --> 01:33:36,519
We'll come back
and look another day, okay?

1476
01:33:45,699 --> 01:33:47,690
<i>[Engine Starts]</i>

1477
